<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1378,1520]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
This species was found on three seamounts and also on the southern slope of 
<collectingCountry box="[1068,1250,1378,1404]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation box="[1266,1367,1378,1404]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,240,689,713]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparative species diversity on the seamounts as sampled by different cruises (Norfolk 1 and Norfolk 2)" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Tables 
<number box="[1352,1367,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.2">1</number>
</tableCitation>
, 2) at depths of 
<quantity box="[273,411,1417,1443]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.13" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="2.76" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="m" value="413.0" valueMax="550.0" valueMin="276.0">276–550 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[429,522,1417,1443]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,194,1278]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,194,1279]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 14. Depth ranges of particular brachiopod species collected during the Norfolk 1 and Norfolk 2 cruises to the Norfolk Ridge, New Caledonia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190412/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[488,522,1417,1443]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). It is reported here the first time from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1054,1150,1417,1443]" name="Norfolk Island" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Norfolk</collectingCountry>
Ridge, although it was already noted from 
<collectingCountry box="[387,572,1456,1482]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Laurin" box="[587,741,1456,1482]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" refString="Laurin, B. (1997) Brachiopodes recoltes dans les eaux de la Nouvelle Caledonie et des iles Loyaute, Matthew et Chesterfield. In: Crosnier, A. (ed.), Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM. Volume 18. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 176, 411 - 471." type="journal article" year="1997">
Laurin 
<number box="[677,741,1456,1482]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[762,951,1456,1481]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="lucida">
<emphasis box="[762,951,1456,1481]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Basiliola lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from off 
<collectingCountry box="[1368,1436,1456,1482]" name="Japan" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hatai" box="[159,293,1494,1520]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" refString="Hatai, K. M. (1940) The Cenozoic Brachiopoda from Japan. The Science Reports of the Tohoku Imperial University, Sendai, Japan, Second Series (Geology), 20, 1 - 413." type="journal article" year="1940">
Hatai 
<number box="[231,293,1494,1520]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1940.0">1940</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper" box="[305,462,1494,1520]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="6" pageNumber="30" refString="Cooper, G. A. (1959) Genera of Tertiary and Recent rhynchonelloid brachiopods. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 139, 1 - 90." type="journal article" year="1959">
Cooper 
<number box="[399,462,1494,1520]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1959.0">1959</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Recently it was also found in the 
<collectingCountry box="[873,914,1494,1520]" name="Fiji" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fiji</collectingCountry>
region (Bitner 
<number box="[1094,1157,1494,1520]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2008.0">2008</number>
).
</paragraph>
